properties.title: Turmoil in Polling Station
properties.description: Turmoil in Polling StationElectoral Precinct 25 of Gardabani Electoral District opened late (at 9:15 a.m.). The control sheet was inserted into the ballot box before the draw. A commission member from the United National Movement has deputized as commission secretary because the actual secretary does not know the official language. There is chaos in the polling station as the commission member responsible for regulating the flow of voters has failed to do so. The information about the control sheet had not been added to the protocol by 10 a.m. though voters were still casting ballots. The Precinct Electoral Commission refused to register an ISFED complaint though it did take a copy. The organization submitted the same complaint to Gardabani District Electoral Commission #21.Time: 2010-05-30 20:44:03Source: ISFEDCategory: Observation Findings - E-DayDistrict: GardabaniPrecinct: 25

properties.title: Observer Asked to Leave Polling Station
properties.description:
Observer Asked to Leave Polling StationIn Electoral Precinct 41 of Rustavi Electoral District, an ISFED observer was subjected to pressure. Gocha Kurdadze, an individual whom the observer had not previously known, phoned the observer and categorically demanded that the observer left the polling station and travelled to vote in his own electoral precinct in a car sent by Kurdadze. The organization conducted an inquiry and determined that the person who had called the
observer was a United National Movement activist. The observer received a second phone
call from the driver, who said that he was waiting outside. Naturally, the organization’s observer did not leave the polling station.Time: 2010-05-30 20:22:41Source: ISFEDCategory: Observation Findings - E-DayDistrict: RustaviPrecinct: 41

properties.title: Observers forced to leave polling station
properties.description: Observers forced to leave polling stationThe inking device was out of order. Voting still began and the control sheet was dropped into the ballot box. Lagodekhi Majoritarian MP Guram Kakalashvili was in the polling station and instructed Precinct Electoral Commission Chairman Adlat Sardarov not to accept complaints. The latter complied with the instruction. There was a group of people outside the polling station who later entered the station and forced observers to leave. There was a security police officer outside the polling station but he did not react to the incident.Time: 2010-05-30 18:45:04Source: TICategory: Observation Findings - E-DayDistrict: LagodekhiPrecinct: 1

properties.title: Potential Fraud With Mobile Ballot Box in Ozurgeti
properties.description: Potential Fraud With Mobile Ballot Box in OzurgetiSeveral statements requesting the use of the mobile ballot box at different addresses have been obtained. Judging by the handwriting, these statements are likely to have been written by the same person. Considering the information escribed above, suspicions arise that the mobile ballot box lists have been rigged in these precincts.Time: 2010-05-30 18:41:23Source: TICategory: Observation Findings - E-DayDistrict: OzurgetiPrecinct: 57

properties.title: People Unjustly Registered as Mobile Ballot Box Users
properties.description: People Unjustly Registered as Mobile Ballot Box UsersIn the voter list supplement, there are 107 voters registered as mobile ballot box users. Many people on the list have said that they are planning to turn up at the polling station and never asked to have the mobile ballot box delivered to their homes. The 107 phone calls requesting inclusion of these individuals on the mobile ballot box list were made from five different phone numbers. Of these numbers, two belong to National Movement coordinators Gela Kalandarishvili and Nodar (last name unknown). They have confirmed that they both phoned the electoral precinct and supplied the data.Time: 2010-05-30 18:37:12Source: TICategory: Observation Findings - E-DayDistrict: OzurgetiPrecinct: 23
